sentence: Thursday's session closes with the NASDAQ Composite Index at 2,986.12.
The total shares traded for the NASDAQ was over 1.87 billion shares traded.
Advancers stocks led declining by 1.38 to 1 ratio.
There were 1446 advancers and 1047 decliners for the day.
On the NASDAQ Stock Exchange 26 stocks reached a 52 week high and 29 those reaching lows totaled.
The most active, advancers, decliners, unusual volume and most active by dollar volume can be monitored intraday on the Most Active Stocks page.
The NASDAQ 100 index closed up .08% for the day; a total of 2.11 points.
F5 Networks, Inc. ( FFIV ) had the largest percent change down (-11.06%) while Micron Technology, Inc. ( MU ) had the largest percent change gain rising 10.06%.
The Dow Jones index closed up .2% for the day; a total of 26.34 points.
Boeing Company (The) ( BA ) had the largest percent change down (-1.61%) while Procter & Gamble Company (The) ( PG ) had the largest percent change gain rising 2.92%.
